 {"id":"sqlmodel_rust-b0q.3","title":"Postgres: Implement connection establishment and state machine","description":"# Task: Implement PostgreSQL Connection and State Machine

## Context
The PostgreSQL connection manages the TCP socket, handles the startup sequence, tracks transaction state, and maintains protocol state. This is the core of the driver.

## Connection State Machine

### States
```
Disconnected -> Connecting -> Authenticating -> Ready -> InQuery -> Ready
                                                     \-> InTransaction -> Ready
```

### State Transitions
```rust
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy)]
pub enum ConnectionState {
    Disconnected,
    Connecting,
    Authenticating,
    Ready(TransactionStatus),
    InQuery,
    InTransaction(TransactionStatus),
    Error,
    Closed,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy)]
pub enum TransactionStatus {
    Idle,        // 'I' - no transaction
    InTrans,     // 'T' - in transaction
    InFailed,    // 'E' - in failed transaction
}
```

